Description: Ostracon, fragment from the body of a buff-coloured pottery wine-jar, fabric has some inclusions, interior slightly grooved and exterior covered with a light-brown coloured slip, with remains of two lines of thickly black-painted hieratic text on the exterior specifying the contents sa year 10 western river wine.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389886) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389886)
